<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,908,1116]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,980,1007]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[383,484,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis box="[383,484,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by the following combination of characters: pronotum entirely covered with coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[568,699,1016,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="23.[151,264,885,910]" captionTargetBox="[371,1212,203,842]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[338,1245,178,862]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Pronotum, group spondiae: 54. A. alternatus, 55. A. cuernavacensis, 56. A. spondiae and 57. A. vitis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557895/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Figs 54–57</figureCitation>
) and elytra with strips of setae. Internal sac in the apical region with a pair of sclerites, median region with a pair of serrate blades at margin and apex and unpaired sclerite (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 103–106" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1589,1614]" captionTargetBox="[251,1338,188,1559]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[238,1349,174,1570]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 103–106. Male genitalia, median lobe, group spondiae: 103. A. alternatus, 104. A. cuernavacensis, 105. A. spondiae and 106. A. vitis. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557911/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Figs 103–106</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
